Creation of Solid Geometry Surface Models for 3D-Printing, Shape Optimization, Topology Optimization (PDE-Toolbox), and Dynamic Simulation (Simscape Multi-Body)

Part E - Frame Concept for Solid Geometries and Macro Language Concept

Tim Lueth - Professor at Technical Universiity of Munich - Germany - 2019
Set Java Heap to 2048 MByte & SG-Lib Rel. 4.6 is required

6 Attaching Frames to Solid Geometries

6.1 Define Frames Linked to Feature-Surfaces

SGofCPLcommand('co 10 50 5, h 6');
SGofCPLcommand('co 10 50 5, h 6')
SGofCPLcommand('co 10 50 5, h 6, fset B 2 30');
SGofCPLcommand('co 10 50 5, h 6, fset B 2 30')
SGofCPLcommand('co 10 50 5, h 6, fset B 2 30 R1');
SGofCPLcommand('co 10 50 5, h 6, fset B 2 30 R1')
SGofCPLcommand('co 10 50 5, h 6, fset B 1 0 R1, fset F 2 0 R2');
SGofCPLcommand('co 10 50 5, h 6, fset B 1 0 R1, fset F 2 0 R2')
SGofCPLcommand(['co 10 50 5, h 6, fset B 1 0 R1, fset F 2 0 R2, enter, scr 4 10 1 ',...
'1, swap, dup, dup, dup']);
SGofCPLcommand('co 10 50 5, h 6, fset B 1 0 R1, fset F 2 0 R2, enter, scr 4 10 1 1, swap, dup, dup, dup')

6.2 Align Solids by Frame Names

SGofCPLcommand('co 10 50 5, h 6, fset B 1 0 R1, fset F 2 0 R2, save A' );
SGofCPLcommand('co 10 50 5, h 6, fset B 1 0 R1, fset F 2 0 R2, save A')
% SGofCPLcommand('load A, dup, col m, falign F B -90');
% UNFORTUNATLEY CURRENTLY LOAD REMOVES THE FRAMES STIL IN REL 4.6

' F B -90, dup, col b, falign F B 30, dup, col g, falign F B 120, cat, cat, cat, ',...
'write open_chain']);

7 Macros for the SG-Coding-Language

7.1 Defining Macros without parameters

SGofCPLcommand('$cyl: c 5, h 4:'); % Defining Macros
==> Macro "$CYL" declared as "c 5, h 4"
SGofCPLcommand('$cyl: c 5, h 4:')
SGofCPLcommand('$cyl: c 5, h 4:, $cyl'); % Defining Macros and use Macros
==> Macro "$CYL" declared as "c 5, h 4" ==> Macro "$CYL" used as "c 5, h 4"
SGofCPLcommand('$cyl: c 5, h 4:, $cyl')

7.2 Defining Macros including parameters

SGofCPLcommand('$cyl: c $1, h $2:'); % Defining Macros
==> Macro "$CYL" declared as "c $1, h $2"
SGofCPLcommand('$cyl: c $1, h $2:')
SGofCPLcommand('$cyl: c $1, h $2:, $cyl 3 10'); % Defining Macros and use Macros
==> Macro "$CYL" declared as "c $1, h $2" ==> Macro "$CYL" used as "c 3, h 10"
SGofCPLcommand('$cyl: c $1, h $2:, $cyl 3 10')
SGofCPLcommand('$cyl: c $1, h $2:, $cyl 3 10, enter, $cyl 6 2, rel ontop, cat');
==> Macro "$CYL" declared as "c $1, h $2" ==> Macro "$CYL" used as "c 3, h 10" ==> Macro "$CYL" used as "c 6, h 2"
SGofCPLcommand('$cyl: c $1, h $2:, $cyl 3 10, enter, $cyl 6 2, rel ontop, cat')
SGofCPLcommand('$cyl: c $1, h $2, fset B 1, fset F 2:, $cyl 3 10');
==> Macro "$CYL" declared as "c $1, h $2, fset B 1, fset F 2" ==> Macro "$CYL" used as "c 3, h 10, fset B 1, fset F 2"
SGofCPLcommand('$cyl: c $1, h $2, fset B 1, fset F 2:, $cyl 3 10')
SGofCPLcommand('$lnk: co 10 $1 5, h 6, fset B 1 0 R1, fset F 2 0 R2 :, $lnk 30');
==> Macro "$LNK" declared as "co 10 $1 5, h 6, fset B 1 0 R1, fset F 2 0 R2" ==> Macro "$LNK" used as "co 10 30 5, h 6, fset B 1 0 R1, fset F 2 0 R2"
SGofCPLcommand('$lnk: co 10 $1 5, h 6, fset B 1 0 R1, fset F 2 0 R2 :, $lnk 30')

7.3 Macros using Frames

SGofCPLcommand(['$lnk: co 10 $1 5, h 6, fset B 1 0 R1, fset F 2 0 R2 :, $lnk 30, d',...
'up, falign B F']);
==> Macro "$LNK" declared as "co 10 $1 5, h 6, fset B 1 0 R1, fset F 2 0 R2" ==> Macro "$LNK" used as "co 10 30 5, h 6, fset B 1 0 R1, fset F 2 0 R2"
SGofCPLcommand('$lnk: co 10 $1 5, h 6, fset B 1 0 R1, fset F 2 0 R2 :, $lnk 30, dup, falign B F')

'nter, $lnk 40, falign B F']);
==> Macro "$LNK" declared as "co 10 $1 5, h 6, fset B 1 0 R1, fset F 2 0 R2" ==> Macro "$LNK" used as "co 10 30 5, h 6, fset B 1 0 R1, fset F 2 0 R2" ==> Macro "$LNK" used as "co 10 40 5, h 6, fset B 1 0 R1, fset F 2 0 R2"
SGofCPLcommand('$lnk: co 10 $1 5, h 6, fset B 1 0 R1, fset F 2 0 R2 :, $lnk 30, enter, $lnk 40, falign B F')

'nter, $lnk 40, falign F B']);
==> Macro "$LNK" declared as "co 10 $1 5, h 6, fset B 1 0 R1, fset F 2 0 R2" ==> Macro "$LNK" used as "co 10 30 5, h 6, fset B 1 0 R1, fset F 2 0 R2" ==> Macro "$LNK" used as "co 10 40 5, h 6, fset B 1 0 R1, fset F 2 0 R2"
SGofCPLcommand('$lnk: co 10 $1 5, h 6, fset B 1 0 R1, fset F 2 0 R2 :, $lnk 30, enter, $lnk 40, falign F B')
SGofCPLcommand(['$lnk: co 10 $1 5, h 6, fset B 1 0 R1, fset F 2 0 R2 :, $lnk 30, e',...
'nter, $lnk 40, falign']);
==> Macro "$LNK" declared as "co 10 $1 5, h 6, fset B 1 0 R1, fset F 2 0 R2" ==> Macro "$LNK" used as "co 10 30 5, h 6, fset B 1 0 R1, fset F 2 0 R2" ==> Macro "$LNK" used as "co 10 40 5, h 6, fset B 1 0 R1, fset F 2 0 R2"
SGofCPLcommand('$lnk: co 10 $1 5, h 6, fset B 1 0 R1, fset F 2 0 R2 :, $lnk 30, enter, $lnk 40, falign')

SGofCPLcommand('$lnk: co 10 $1 5, h 6, fset B 1 0 R1, fset F 2 0 R2 :, $lnk 30, enter, $lnk 40, falign F B 45')

7.4 Preloading the SGCL-Interpreter with Solids and Contours and Macros

SGofCPLcommand('','',{},SGbox(30),PLcircle(10)); VLFLplotlight (1,.5); % Preload SG and Preload CPL
SGofCPLcommands supports the following commands, separated by commas: See publishable tutorial VLFL_EXP45.m === CPL shape commands ================================= b x-size y-size [d] => Box as rectangle or displace trapaze c diameter diameter edges => Cylinder or ellipse as polygon cs phi r-outer r-inner offset => Cylinder segment with angle co r-outer length r-inner => Cylinder oval segment with optional holes d diameter x-coord y-coord n-faces => Drilling hole at x/y with n edges g diameter teeth-nr turn => Gear that it turned (f.i. 0.5 teeth) ms diameter-1 diameter-2 => Motor shaft contour === CPL manipulation commands ================================= move x-coord y-coord => Move the CPL relatively cp x-coord y-coord => Center point change ch distance radius => Convex hull in distance with optional radius dupc x-copies y copies distance => Duplicates contour in as x y pattern dupr radius number offset => Duplicates contour radial in n copies rad radius => Radial edges (+r) or cuts (-r) at each corner rot degree x y => Rotate a contour ccw by degree on centerpoint x y, default is center of CPL === CPL stack commands ================================= enter => current CPL is shifted to the stack dup => current CPL is duplicated to the stack swap => current CPL is swaped with CPL on stack +/add => current CPL is added to stack CPL -/sub => current CPL is substracted from stack CPL rem => stack CPL ist substracted from current CPL &/isec => current CPL is intersected with stack CPL hs height => stack connection using height === CPL to solid commands ================================= h height z-displacement => Height of the extruded solid hc height z-displacement => Height of extrusion with smoothed edges r angle pitch => Extrusion by rotation (degree) and optional pitch === SG element commands ================================= scr mm length diameter => Screw/Cutter/Nut threat of diameter and length sph diameter end-angle => Sphere === SG manipulation commands ================================= move x-coord y-coord => Move the solid relatively cham rar upper-dist lower-dist => Chamfer the edges of a 2.5 solid rotx degree => rotate around the x-axis roty degree => rotate around the y-axis rotz degree => rotate around the z-axis melt => Boolean addition of all solid elements text string => Add a string to the largest surface dupr number => Duplicates solids radial in n copies dups nx ny nz d => Duplicates solid spatial in x y z with distance d dupg nx ny nz d => Duplicates solid on a grid in x y z with distance d hollow wall => Creates a hollow solid shell wall distance => Creates a shell for the solid cutz z1 z2 => Cuts the solid at z1 and z2 === SG save and restore commands ================================= save name => saves the solid into name.SG load name => loads a solid from name.SG write name => saves the solid into File name.STL read name => reads the solid from File name.STL mag fact => magnifies the current solid col color => colors the faces of the current solid === SG stack commands ================================= enter => current SG is shifted to the stack dup => current SG is duplicated to the stack swap => current SG is swaped with SG on stack clear nr => Clear stack content 1..n +/add => current SG is added to stack SG -/sub => current SG is substracted from stack SG rem => stack SG is substracted from current SG &/isec => current SG is intersected with stack SG rel command parameter => current SG is move relatively to stack === Frame commands ================================= fset name ident rotation feature => attach a frame to the current SG falign Stack-Frame SG-Frame degree => align current SG-frame with stack frame and rotate === Macro commands ================================= $cmd: <string>: => Define macro using $1 $2 $3 $4 as parameters $cmd $1 $2 $3 $4 => Use macro as command with $1 $2 $3 $4 as parameters Try: SGofCPLcommand('g 3 22, h 5, c 5, h 20, roty -90, move 10 10') Try: SGofCPLcommand('$cob: co $1 $2 $3, h $3, fset B 1 0 R1, fset F 2 0 R2:, $cob 10 50 5, dup, falign F B 45')
SGofCPLcommand('?')
SGofCPLcommand('enter','',{},SGbox(30),PLcircle(10)); % CPL is prioritized at stack operations
SGofCPLcommand('enter')
SGofCPLcommand('enter, enter','',{},SGbox(30),PLcircle(10)); % Preloaded CPL SG on stack operations
SGofCPLcommand('enter, enter')
SGofCPLcommand('c 50, h 60','',{},SGbox(30)); % Normal interpreter mode after preloading
SGofCPLcommand('c 50, h 60')
e=[{'$LNK'},{'co 10 $1 5, h 6, fset B 1 0 R1, fset F 2 0 R2'};...
{'$ADDLNK'},{'enter, co 10 $1 5, h 6, fset B 1 0 R1, fset F 2 0 R2'}]
e = 22 cell array
{'$LNK' } {'co 10 $1 5, h 6, fset B 1 0 R1, fset F 2 0 R2' } {'$ADDLNK'} {'enter, co 10 $1 5, h 6, fset B 1 0 R1, fset F 2 0 R2'}
SGofCPLcommand('enter','',e,SGbox(30),PLcircle(10));
SGofCPLcommand('enter')

7.5 Macros using Macros

SGofCPLcommand(['$lnk: co 10 $1 5, h 6, fset B 1 0 R1, fset F 2 0 R2 :, $e: enter,',...
' $lnk 90, enter :, $lnk 30, $e, $lnk 40, falign F B 30']);
==> Macro "$LNK" declared as "co 10 $1 5, h 6, fset B 1 0 R1, fset F 2 0 R2" ==> Macro "$E" declared as "enter, $lnk 90, enter" ==> Macro "$LNK" used as "co 10 30 5, h 6, fset B 1 0 R1, fset F 2 0 R2" ==> Macro "$LNK" used as "co 10 90 5, h 6, fset B 1 0 R1, fset F 2 0 R2" ==> Macro "$E" used as "enter, $lnk 90, enter" ==> Macro "$LNK" used as "co 10 40 5, h 6, fset B 1 0 R1, fset F 2 0 R2"
SGofCPLcommand('$lnk: co 10 $1 5, h 6, fset B 1 0 R1, fset F 2 0 R2 :, $e: enter, $lnk 90, enter :, $lnk 30, $e, $lnk 40, falign F B 30')
SGofCPLcommand(['$lnk: co 10 $1 5, h 6, fset B 1 0 R1, fset F 2 0 R2 :, $addlnk: e',...
'nter, $lnk $1, falign F B $2:, $lnk 30, $addlnk 50 45, $addlnk 40 45, cat, cat'])
==> Macro "$LNK" declared as "co 10 $1 5, h 6, fset B 1 0 R1, fset F 2 0 R2" ==> Macro "$ADDLNK" declared as "enter, $lnk $1, falign F B $2" ==> Macro "$LNK" used as "co 10 30 5, h 6, fset B 1 0 R1, fset F 2 0 R2" ==> Macro "$LNK" used as "co 10 50 5, h 6, fset B 1 0 R1, fset F 2 0 R2" ==> Macro "$ADDLNK" used as "enter, $lnk 50, falign F B 45" ==> Macro "$LNK" used as "co 10 40 5, h 6, fset B 1 0 R1, fset F 2 0 R2" ==> Macro "$ADDLNK" used as "enter, $lnk 40, falign F B 45"
SGofCPLcommand('$lnk: co 10 $1 5, h 6, fset B 1 0 R1, fset F 2 0 R2 :, $addlnk: enter, $lnk $1, falign F B $2:, $lnk 30, $addlnk 50 45, $addlnk 40 45, cat, cat')
